claim:
Log-transformed biomarker data were evaluated by a linear mixed-effects model, with visit variable as a fixed effect and patient as a random effect to determine whether on-study biomarker levels at weeks 4, 12, and 24 differed from baseline, with two-sided 95% confidence intervals.Results
Patient Disposition
A total of 31 patients with IPF receiving background pirfenidone were screened, of whom 10 were deemed ineligible (Fig. 2).

caption: Patient disposition. FEV1 forced expiratory volume in 1 s, FVC forced vital capacity, HRCT high-resolution computed tomography, IPF idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis

claim: No meaningful change from baseline was observed at weeks 4, 12, and 24 after vismodegib treatment (Fig. 3).
title: Fig. 3.
caption: Individual CXCL14 levels. Plasma CXCL14 levels in individuals over time after initiation of vismodegib treatment.
